```
std::string convert_markdown_to_html(const std::string& markdown_text) {
    std::string html_text;

    // Loop through each character in the markdown text
    for (char c : markdown_text) {
        // Check if the current character is a special character that needs to be escaped
        if (c == '#' || c == '*' || c == '_' || c == '`') {
            html_text += "&" + c + ";";
        } else {
            html_text += c;
        }
    }

    return html_text;
}
```

This function uses a for loop to iterate through each character in the markdown_text string. For each character, it checks if it is a special character that needs to be escaped (i.e. #, *, _, or `). If it is, the function replaces the character with its corresponding HTML entity (&#, **, __, or ```). Otherwise, it simply adds the character to the html_text string. Finally, the function returns the resulting HTML formatted text.

